 2 crystal slide jars, each filled with xylene.


 Antibody cocktails:


 Appropriate antibody concentrations should be determined prior to dissection through titrations and 30 second staining incubations.  We found PE fluorochromes degraded too quickly using the Arcturus LCM system, while FITC and Alexa-647 fluorochromes were suitable for our use.  However, all three fluors \(PE, FITC, and Alexa-647) work well with the Leica system.  The cocktails used in our studies were:


40&#xB5;l CD4-Alexa647 \(1:5, Caltag);       


4&#xB5;l Gr1-FITC \(1:50, BD Pharmingen);


1&#xB5;l Rnasin \(400unit/ml, Invitrogen);       


Q.C. to 200&#xB5;l with PBS





And





5&#xB5;l F4/80-Alexa647 \(1:40, Caltag)    


1&#xB5;l Rnasin \(400unit/ml, Invitrogen)           


Q.C. to 200&#xB5;l with PBS
